.TH "ima_inode_post_setattr" 9 "ima_inode_post_setattr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ima_inode_post_setattr \- reflect file metadata changes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ima_inode_post_setattr
.BI "(struct user_namespace *mnt_userns "  ","
.BI "struct dentry *dentry "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mnt_userns" 12
user namespace of the mount the inode was found from
.IP "dentry" 12
pointer to the affected dentry
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Changes to a dentry's metadata might result in needing to appraise.

This function is called from \fBnotify_change\fP, which expects the caller
to lock the inode's i_mutex.
